{"questionId":"11763","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Beth goes for a run. She uses a fitness app to record her distance, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n</math></span> km, and time, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> minutes. A graph of her distance against time is shown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/9b0dc42c50234d45f5e8eeb2bca3c40136e3ff8f.png\"></p>\n<p>Beth runs at a constant speed of 2.3 ms<sup>–1</sup>&nbsp;for the first 8 minutes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Between 8 and 20 minutes, her distance can be modeled by a cubic function,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s = a{t^3} + b{t^2} + ct + d\">\n  <mi>s</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;She reads the following data from her app.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/fa825027346bbd299e8abd1d5da85305474a1427.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>either using a cubic regression or solving a system of 4 equations&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a =&nbsp; - 0.00364{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b = 0.150{\\text{,}}\\,\\,c =&nbsp; - 1.67{\\text{,}}\\,\\,d = 6.72\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0.00364</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.150</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1.67</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6.72</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11763","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.13b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of a , b , c and d .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}